Taiwan one - month NCD average yield at 5 . 605 pct . Taiwan ' s central bank issued T $ 5 billion in one - day negotiable certificates of deposit on Thursday at an average yield of 5 . 605 percent , a central bank official said . The range of the bids was between 5 . 600 and 5 . 610 percent . Demand totalled T $ 14 . 7 billion . The central bank repeatedly issued NCDs during a sustained stock rally in March and April , a move widely seen as aiming to keep a lid on the loose liquidity that many experts said had been fuelling the sizzling stock market . The central bank has confirmed that it was responding to the liquidity sitution but denied that it was acting directly in response to the stock market bull run . - - Taipei Newsroom ( 2 - 5080815 ) 
